------------------------------------------------

# Core

Everything must go through Core.

Modules NEVER execute mysql directly.

Modules talk to MariaDB only through dispatcher_driver_* APIs.

core/driver.sh is internal to Core.

MariaDB-specific logic lives only in drivers/mariadb.sh.

------------------------------------------------

# Modules

Each module is a package under modules/<name>/module.sh.

Each module has ONE responsibility.

users

permissions

database

backup

restore

monitor

security

settings

plugins

theme

------------------------------------------------

# Maximum File Size

Maximum 350 lines per file.

If larger

Split.

------------------------------------------------

# Functions

Maximum 30 lines.

One responsibility.

Document every function.

------------------------------------------------

# Naming

snake_case only.

No camelCase.

------------------------------------------------

# Shell

Use Bash 5+

Enable

set -Eeuo pipefail

Use strict mode.

------------------------------------------------

# UI

Prefer

dialog

Fallback

whiptail

Fallback

plain terminal

Never depend on only one UI.

------------------------------------------------

# Theme Engine

Every color comes from theme files.

Never hardcode ANSI colors.

------------------------------------------------

# Logging

Everything logs.

logs/manager.log

Log Levels

INFO

WARN

ERROR

DEBUG

------------------------------------------------

# Config

Everything configurable.

config/config.conf

------------------------------------------------

# Error Handling

Never ignore errors.

Never use

|| true

unless absolutely required.

------------------------------------------------

# SQL

Never concatenate unsafe SQL.

Escape identifiers.

Always validate user input.

------------------------------------------------

# Security

No plaintext passwords in logs.

Mask passwords.

Confirm dangerous operations.

------------------------------------------------

# Plugin System

Plugins live in

plugins/

Plugins auto load.

------------------------------------------------

# Coding Style

Readable.

Clean.

Self documented.

ShellCheck clean.

shfmt formatted.

------------------------------------------------

# Git

Small commits.

Atomic commits.

Meaningful messages.

------------------------------------------------

# Documentation

Every public function must have comments.

README always updated.

------------------------------------------------

# Testing

Every module should have tests when possible.

------------------------------------------------

# Performance

Avoid useless subprocesses.

Avoid unnecessary cat.

Prefer builtins.

------------------------------------------------

# Goal

This project should become the best open-source terminal MariaDB manager.